text: Naâma Province () is a province (wilaya) of Algeria named after its provincial seat, the town of Naâma. The region is dominated by a large sabkha. There is an airport in Mécheria. ==Administrative divisions== The province is divided into 7 districts (daïras), which are further divided into 12 communes or municipalities. ===Districts=== thumb|upright=1.5|center| ===Communes=== center # Naâma # Mécheria # Aïn Séfra # Tiout # Sfissifa # Moghrar # Asla # Djéniane Bourzeg # Aïn Ben Khelil # Mekmen Ben Amar # Kasdir # El Biod ==References== Category:Provinces of Algeria
